You are building Service 4: the Frontend for an Engineering Impact Dashboard. Working directory is D:\Projects\WorkWeave\frontend\.

Create a Next.js + Tailwind CSS single-page dashboard. It reads from `public/results.json` (Contract C schema below) and displays the top 5 most impactful PostHog engineers.

**IMPORTANT INSTRUCTIONS:**
1. First, initialize the Next.js project: `cd D:/Projects/WorkWeave && npx create-next-app@latest frontend --typescript --tailwind --eslint --app --no-src-dir --import-alias "@/*" --use-npm` (answer yes to all prompts, use `--yes` or pipe yes)
2. Then create all components
3. Create a mock `results.json` in `frontend/public/` for development
4. Make sure `npm run build` succeeds

**Contract C: results.json schema** that the page reads:
```json
{
  "metadata": {
    "generated_at": "2026-03-22T10:20:00Z",
    "period": { "start": "2025-12-22", "end": "2026-03-22" },
    "total_prs_analyzed": 1247,
    "total_engineers": 85,
    "model_used": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"
  },
  "methodology": {
    "summary": "Impact scored across 4 pillars: Contribution (40%), Review (25%), Velocity (20%), Breadth (15%)",
    "pillars": {
      "contribution_impact": {
        "weight": 0.40,
        "description": "Sum of PR quality scores (complexity, scope, type, risk, novelty). Quality over quantity.",
        "pr_formula": "complexity*0.25 + scope*0.30 + type_weight*0.20 + risk*0.15 + novelty*0.10"
      },
      "review_impact": {
        "weight": 0.25,
        "description": "Sum of review quality scores, weighted by the importance of the PR being reviewed.",
        "review_formula": "(depth*0.40 + detection*0.35 + constructiveness*0.25) * pr_impact/10"
      },
      "collaboration_velocity": {
        "weight": 0.20,
        "description": "How quickly an engineer reviews others' code and incorporates feedback on their own."
      },
      "codebase_breadth": {
        "weight": 0.15,
        "description": "Number of distinct codebase zones (frontend, backend API, models, analytics, etc.) touched."
      }
    },
    "final_formula": "contribution*0.40 + review*0.25 + velocity*0.20 + breadth*0.15 -> 0-100"
  },
  "engineers": [
    {
      "rank": 1,
      "login": "engineer_a",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1234",
      "final_score": 87.3,
      "pillars": {
        "contribution_impact": {
          "score": 92.1,
          "raw_total": 287.5,
          "pr_count": 34,
          "dominant_type": "feature"
        },
        "review_impact": {
          "score": 78.5,
          "raw_total": 156.3,
          "review_count": 67
        },
        "collaboration_velocity": {
          "score": 85.0,
          "median_review_turnaround_hours": 3.2,
          "median_feedback_incorporation_hours": 5.1
        },
        "codebase_breadth": {
          "score": 87.5,
          "zones_touched": ["frontend/", "posthog/api/", "posthog/models/", "ee/clickhouse/"],
          "zones_total": 8
        }
      },
      "top_prs": [
        {
          "number": 12345,
          "title": "Add cohort-based feature flags",
          "url": "https://github.com/PostHog/posthog/pull/12345",
          "type_classification": "feature",
          "composite": 8.45,
          "scores": { "complexity": 8, "scope_of_impact": 9, "type_weight": 9, "risk_and_judgment": 7, "novelty": 8 },
          "one_line_summary": "Adds ability to target feature flags at behavioral cohorts",
          "reasoning": "High complexity: introduces CohortMatcher with recursive resolution..."
        }
      ],
      "top_reviews": [
        {
          "pr_number": 12400,
          "pr_title": "Refactor event processing pipeline",
          "url": "https://github.com/PostHog/posthog/pull/12400",
          "weighted_composite": 6.55,
          "scores": { "review_depth": 8, "issue_detection": 7, "constructiveness": 8 },
          "reasoning": "Identified recursive cohort edge case and suggested fix"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**Design Requirements:**
- Single page that fits on a laptop screen
- Clean, professional look (dark or light - your choice, but make it polished)
- Top 5 engineer cards showing: rank, avatar, GitHub username, final score, four pillar scores as horizontal bars
- Each card is expandable (click to toggle) — expanded view shows:
  - Top PRs with type badges, composite score, one-line summary, link to GitHub
  - Top reviews with scores and reasoning
  - Codebase zones touched
- A "Methodology" section (collapsible accordion) at the bottom explaining the scoring formula
- Every score should be understandable — use labels, not just numbers
- GitHub links on PR titles (open in new tab)
- Show the date range from metadata
- Type badges for PRs: feature (blue), bugfix-critical (red), bugfix-minor (orange), refactor (purple), performance (green), etc.

**Create mock data** with 5 realistic-looking engineers with varied scores to test the layout.

**Tech:** Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS, no additional libraries needed. Keep it simple.

Write ALL the code. Make sure it builds successfully. Do NOT leave any TODOs.

